<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-11-29T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-11-29T12:00:00-05:00" n="1011" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1011">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">823.001 Sanchez Cerro, Luis/41:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Peru</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Dearing</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Lima</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-11-29T12:00:00-05:00">November 29,
                                1931—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 2 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>367. The National Electoral Board yesterday officially proclaimed Sanchez
                            Cerro elected President of Peru by 152,000 votes out of 299,000. The
                            Constituent Assembly held its first meeting and organized.</p>
                        <pb facs="1043" n="923" xml:id="pg_923"/>
                        <p>The National Electoral Board has completed its work and terminated.</p>
                        <p>Sanchez Cerro should take oath of office the 8th or 9th of December.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Dearing</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>